sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as Admission Webhook<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as KubeRay Operator<br/>SA Token Auth
    participant Kubelet as Kubelet
    participant Registry as Container Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod<br/>User: 1000
    participant WorkerPod as Ray Worker Pod<br/>User: 1000
    participant Redis as External Redis<br/>6379/TCP Optional
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over User,WorkerPod: Flow 1: RayCluster Creation
        User->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster CR<br/>kubectl apply<br/>Auth: User credentials
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate RayCluster<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>TLS 1.2+
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation result<br/>Success/Failure
        K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event<br/>RayCluster created
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>SA Token
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Role/RoleBinding<br/>HTTPS/6443
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Service<br/>6379,8265,10001,8080
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Head Pod<br/>HTTPS/6443
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/6443
        Kubelet->>Registry: Pull Ray images<br/>HTTPS/443<br/>Pull credentials
        Registry-->>Kubelet: Ray container images
        Note over HeadPod: Ray Head starts<br/>GCS on 6379<br/>Dashboard on 8265
        WorkerPod->>HeadPod: Connect to GCS<br/>6379/TCP<br/>Optional password
        HeadPod-.->Redis: GCS fault tolerance<br/>6379/TCP<br/>Optional TLS
    end

    rect rgb(255, 250, 240)
        Note over User,WorkerPod: Flow 2: RayJob Submission
        User->>K8sAPI: Create RayJob CR<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>User credentials
        K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event<br/>RayJob created
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>SA Token
        Note over Operator,WorkerPod: RayCluster creation flow (as above)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Job Submitter Pod<br/>K8s Job
        Kubelet->>Registry: Pull job image<br/>HTTPS/443
        Note over HeadPod: Job Submitter Pod runs
        HeadPod->>HeadPod: Submit job via Dashboard<br/>HTTP/8265<br/>Optional auth
        HeadPod->>HeadPod: GCS schedules tasks<br/>6379/TCP
        HeadPod->>WorkerPod: Distribute tasks<br/>TCP (various ports)
        WorkerPod-->>HeadPod: Task results
        HeadPod-->>User: Job completes
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Delete RayCluster<br/>Auto-cleanup
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Client,WorkerPod: Flow 3: Ray Serve Request
        Client->>Route: HTTPS/443<br/>POST /predict<br/>TLS 1.2+<br/>Optional Bearer token
        Route->>HeadPod: HTTP/8000<br/>Forward to Serve
        HeadPod->>HeadPod: Ray Serve processes<br/>Port: 8000
        HeadPod->>WorkerPod: Distribute inference<br/>TCP (internal)
        WorkerPod-->>HeadPod: Inference results
        HeadPod-->>Route: JSON response<br/>HTTP/8000
        Route-->>Client: HTTPS/443<br/>Prediction result
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 255)
        Note over Prometheus,Operator: Flow 4: Metrics Collection
        Prometheus->>Operator: Scrape /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080<br/>No auth
        Operator-->>Prometheus: Operator metrics<br/>controller_runtime_*
        Prometheus->>HeadPod: Scrape /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080
        HeadPod-->>Prometheus: Ray cluster metrics<br/>raycluster_*
    end
